Disclaimer
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

LanEx displays output produced by the third-party EDA tools listed above and
performs no silicon analysis of its own. Every metric, report, and verdict it
shows originates from those tools and is passed through unmodified.

LanEx is NOT a sign-off tool. It does not replace foundry sign-off. Before
committing a design to fabrication, you must verify all results against your
foundry's official sign-off decks and your shuttle/MPW program's checks.

LanEx is under active development and testing. Although it passes tool output
through unmodified, the possibility of a display or data-parsing error cannot be
fully excluded. If you intend to manufacture, run the LibreLane flow directly,
independent of LanEx, and base your decision on its native output. Treat LanEx as
a convenience layer over the tools, not a replacement for their authoritative
results; you assume all risk of relying on it. This is a safeguard for the
irreversible step of committing silicon and does not diminish LanEx's day-to-day
accuracy.

